Whatever the formal motivations of any cultural movement whatsoever, human nature will find a way to turn it into a drama society.

The operation in Masonic Arithmetic known as 'digital reduction' is exactly the numerical part (or meta-numerical reflex) of gematria numerization in general. Just as gematria treats all anagrams as equivalences, so -- also -- then with anagrammatic numbers (such as 137 and 173).

... Among the Gematro ciphers, AQ is unusual for being perfectly reliable as a digital reduction engine, which says much about its broader reliability. By comparison, the insights evoked by Synx are wild and delirious.
... When Synx does 'digital reduction' it comes to strange conclusions, which -- while abnormal -- should perhaps be appreciated for their haunting suggestiveness. (666 = 21.)

A decimal digital reduction calculator for numbers of any modulus up to mod-36. ...
